{
  "stem": "24364.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And I think it was in August of '42-- somehow sounds right to me-- that about almost a hundred of them left.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And there were a couple of officers who went to London.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And the rest went to the Middle East, Africa.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And actually, about 30 of them deserted in Palestine, which was rather unpleasant.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "But somehow, it could be understood.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "They never knew whether they could return there and they were there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And most of them eventually joined the Jewish Brigade, so it was really not because they were afraid to-- of the fighting, but because, I guess, also people in the kibbutzim talked them into it, and so they did.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And the Czechs actually were quite nice.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "They really didn't prosecute them, so maybe they could understand it, too.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had a radio and we could listen to the BBC.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there were some newspapers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, you know, most of us-- at least the Czech [? transcript ?] spoke some English and spoke some French, so we could get newspapers.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- but the main thing, there was a central radio, which every time, every day, even, we had news.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When there were news, we could listen to them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so we knew exactly what was going on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, I probably less than many others, because I wasn't that interested at that time yet.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But we knew exactly what was happening to the-- to the war.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we-- the-- the authorities, the camp authorities, I mean our authorities were trying all the time to make the British change their mind, to let us back into-- into Palestine.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they tried to convince them that they did the wrong thing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they wrote letters to London and wrote letters all over the place.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
